args: Fitting complete...and she's ready to go.
Aye, but that feels fine, so it does.\nMe arm swings free'n easy!
Right. Movin' on to the next test.\nStonetech engine...full power!
Holy snot! She just split that boulder\nin two like it was a pat of warm butter!
Aye, and it's all thanks to ye lasses.\nI'd never have been able to finish\nsuch a machine by me lonesome.
Exactly! When you work together, \nyour power goes beyond the limits \nof what any single person can do.
Now let's go save that engineer!
Of course we are!\nIt's all for one and one for all!
Nay, lass, I can't allow it.\nThe mission is far too dangerous.
Okay, did we not JUST get done going\non about how working together makes\nyou stronger than working alone?
It's the same for fighting as it is for\nsmithing, so just accept our help already!
Aye, you're right. In that case,\nI thank ye once again.
I think the engineers are\nbein' held in this mine.
Wait, look! The entrance is guarded!
Can't you, like, tunnel through the\nwalls with your Smithy Arm?
Aye, in theoryâ€”but I'm worried about the\nenergy supply. I don't know how long\nof a tunnel I'd be able to make.
Plus, there's likely to be enemies inside,\nso I'd like to save as much energy as I can.
Good point. We're all in trouble if that\nthing conks out the moment we break in.
In that case, we'll distract them at the\nentrance while you sneak inside.
Oh, I am GREAT at making distractions!
They will regret the day they ever\ncame up with this awful plan.
You ready for your part, Lazry?
It's the enemy! To arms! To arm!
Come and get it! We're quite used to\nhandling a crowd of customers!
Thanks, lasses. I won't let ye down.
Gotta make sure no one spots me...
So, uh, apparently we're under attack.\nShould we go up and help, oooooor...?
Hell noâ€”let the other guards handle it.\nBesides, if we all run up to help,\nwho's gonna guard the engineers?
Right then. Time to see what\nme arm can do!
Aye, and I've come to save everyone!
Er, why aren't ye movin', cousin?
I'm sorry, but...I'm staying.\nThere's something I have to do.
Are ye daft? The Empire soldiers\nwill be back any second!
I am willing to risk my life for the\nsake of my pride as an engineer.
We rokkans build machinery in order\nto help people, not hurt them.
So I can't leave until I destroy the\nterrible machine they made us build!
Nay, I'll take care of the machine.\nMake your escape while ye can.
But you'll be rushing headlong into\nthe enemy! You're likely to die!
No one is dyin' today, cousin.\nNot so long as I have...THIS!
Holy cow. You finished your machine!
Aye, with help from the same friends who\nare outside fightin' for ye right now.
When they found out ye were in trouble,\nthey pitched in to help make this arm...\nand taught me something important.
That's a favor that needs repaid,\nand I'll use me new strength to do it.
So when I say I'll destroy that machine,\nit's a promise ye can trust!
I think I underestimated you.\nYou're a smith for true.
Okay, I'm outta here. Good luck!
*huff* *puff* They just keep comin'...\nI'll never reach the weapon at this rate.
Which means I only got one choice!
Ack! Guys, I think something just\nexploded down in the mine!

See that mana light coming up the shaft?
The weapon we were working on used
that exact type of mana in its reactor,
which means it must have...exploded.
She's safe. She has to be.
She promised to compete against us in\nthe next Golden Anvil, and she's not\nthe type to break a promise.
How in the name of quartz did you\nmanage to survive that explosion?
There were too many soldiers for me to\nreach your weapon, so I decided to throw\na rock into its reactor instead.
Wait, you can't break a reactor with a rock.\n...Unleeeess you have that arm of yours!
Aye! It let me throw the rock from\na safe distance, then skedaddle\non outta there.
Ye said machines are supposed to help\nfolks, and that's just what me arm did.

I was wrong to ever doubt you, Lazry.
You saved countless people AND
protected the pride of engineers
and smiths everywhere!
Which means the debt is paid\nfor your savin' me life.
But I still got a promise to keep\nto the three lasses.
Darn right you do. We'll see you\nat the Golden Anvil!
